		<a href="mailto:talisman17@hotmail.com" target="_new">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/email.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Email Talisman" width="24" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=122&FN=Smithing&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=372286&TN=Bronze+vs+banded&CAT=Trade+Skills&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=372286&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">An interesting thing happened to me the other day. I was auctioning banded suits, and this character messaged me asking if i wanted to trade one for a bronze suit. I immediately took the offer and asked why the hell she was doing this, she told me bronze was just too heavy for her character. Later, I was making another suit and needed to buy some ore and I accidently clicked on the bronze breast plate, to my amazement the selling price was identical to a banded mail of the same size. Banded is worth just as much as bronze! The AC is at most 2 less than bronze, and weighs about half as much, do the math, which is more efficent. Guys, I know it wont catch on for a while, but we gotta spread the word. Jack up your prices! Eventually we may be able to sell our forged armor for as much as that dense, vomit-colored crap.<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
