		<hr size="1">I agree with Talisman<P>I have an agility of 105 and that is worth more to me than the extra couple of ac a bronze suit gives - with a strength of 75 iI need to be as light as possible.  I have fought along bronzed warriors and take less damage because my agility, even though i have less ac.  One secret to keeping weight down is not to use backpacks (3.0 wght) and boxes (2.0 weight), try fletching and sewing kits (0.4 weight each).  Makes a difference getting those extra belts and pads without losing agility.<P>In addition, if you are encumbered, plan on failing in your trades, it quickly reduces your ability to smith, fletch, etc...<P>Fleet of foot rather than plodding along<P>Bladin <BR>Wood Elf Ranger of the 14th Season<BR>Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
