		<hr size="1">I can confirm that there is still a market for banded, especially as replacement for bronze.<P>I have just recently sold 2 full suits of banded because my customers wanted to replace their bronze armor. It was just too heavy.<P>I would urge all smiths and also people who sell off their banded armor not to ruin the market by selling it at low prices. Everybody who has gone all the way to Master Smith will know what it means to try and get even by selling banded armor.<P>Banded armor is NOT some cheap inferior armor to bronze. Bronze is highly overrated.<P>Smiths out there - charge reasonably for our out fine craftsmanship - dont rip people off but also dont ruin the market. My experience shows that customers are quite willing to pay a reasonable amount of money for our very good armor.<P>------------------<BR>Aelven<BR>Druid on Innoruuk<BR>Master Smith<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
