		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=122&FN=Smithing&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=372286&TN=Bronze+vs+banded&CAT=Trade+Skills&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=372295&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I don't know who put this unsubstantiable argument with 1pp per AC in the EQ-world, but it still floats around and no matter how much we smiths try to rectify it it haunts us like some dwarven ghost.<P>Making banded armor is NOT implemented in a way that we can charge 1pp per AC - current raw material prices do not allow us to do so.<P>With this example I will try once again to explain the current pricing structure:<P>A banded bracer has AC 6 - you need one metal sheet to make it and a mold that cost a few gold - this item is trivial below a skill level of 100 - I hardly fail to make a bracer at skill 126<P>A banded cloak has AC 7 - you need 2 metal sheets and a mold that costs roughtly 1pp - cloaks become trivial at around 168 which means you will fail a lot making it.<P>The AC value of banded has no relation to the raw material price or the difficulty of making the item<P>So why on earth should we sell a banded cloak for 7pp???? If you fail just once, which will happen almost certainly below skill 168, we just get even with the used raw materials.<P>Certainly nobody started a trade skill with the idea in mind, supplying others with items for the raw material price - the idea is to make some money.<P>I hope this clarifies the myth of the 1pp per AC for banded. Please believe what masters of their trade try to explain to you and not in some unfounded rumours that were introduced by who knows who.<P>I believe that most people with a trade skill out there dont try to rip off other players but to make a decent living.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Aelven<BR>Druid on Innoruuk<BR>Master Smith<P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
