		<hr size="1">I have recently become a master smith (I achieved 102 last night!).  The situation I find myself in is this. In order to achieve the level of Master by lvl 15, I have spent virtually all my surplus platinum on smithing (after buying spells and other necessities).  This has left me unable to upgrade my own armor; as a matter of fact, I still wear raw hide.  Now I am at a level where I hope to be able to shortly smith my own banded, thereby greatly improving my armor class and my ability to tank.<BR>My point is this: I have sacrificed a great deal to become a master smith while remaining untwinked. In addition to this, I have spent a number of hours standing at the forge when I could have been adventuring (which I actually enjoyed more than I thought I would). But I am now level 14 (I also lost my level last night) and totally broke. I'm on my way out to adventure in order to secure enough platinum to make my first sets of banded armor (already had some success and a lot of failure), and I'll be damned if I'm going to sell it for a loss.  Those that don't want to pay will simply have to find themselves another smith. I have worked too hard and too long to sell my wares for less than I feel they're worth.  If anyone sees my prices and decides they want to become a master smith themselves, they can be my guest, expect to drop 150 + platinum and spend a great number of hours working over a hot forge. <BR>Don't get me wrong, I'm not out to gouge newbies, I plan to charge what I feel to be fair and reasonable prices for my wares, but I (only just now a master smith) am rapidly tiring of this lame argument that "if you don't lower your prices, I'll become a master smith myself." Any trade skill master has worked a great number of hours, and probably sacrificed upgrades for himself to become a master.  If you don't wish to respect that, fine, but I sell for my prices, not yours.<P>Beowulfe (soon to be Grendelbane)<BR>Barbarian Shaman on the 14th  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/frown.gif"> Totem<BR>Master Smith trained exclusively in Halas<BR>Quellious Server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
