		<hr size="1">Well, someone selling something via a trade skill must always try to make a profit and must keep in mind that selling at market value will bring far more customers than selling at higher price and that may result in a far greater profit in after a while.<P>Of course, the first few items(or set if armor pieces) will barely cover what it costed you to train your skill but eventualy, if the demand is there, your training will not only have costed you nothing but you will make significant profit.<P>Always judge if the market value of something will at least cover your failure. If not, don't bother.<P>The main problem with trade skill is that most of the items made are not expendable and twinking hurts trade skills badly.<P>To get back to banded, the market value is 1pp per AC. Sell enough of the tough pieces and you'll get your training money back.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
